::Prowl::

Prowl nods at Iris' comment, trying to calm down a bit. He makes 
himself think of the time they had spent in Iron Raptor's quarters 
back when the Ark was still functional, but it only makes his 
sparkbeat speed up with the memory.

He gives up trying to calm himself down and insted leans forward to 
rest a bit on Iron Raptor, taking comfort from the feeling of her 
moving under him.

THe screen he was carrying nearly drops out of his hands, Prowl 
catching it just in time.

"Sorry," he says to Iris, getting a better grip.
